article.headline: UALR 62, North Texas 57
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Will Neighbour, Josh Hagins and James White scored 11 points apiece and UALR defeated North Texas 62-57 Saturday night. Neighbour also led UALR with six rebounds and four steals. The win was the third straight for the Trojans (14-9, 8-4 Sun Belt) and gave them a season sweep of the Mean Green. Jordan Williams led all scorers with 22 points, and Roger Franklin had 20 points and 12 rebounds for North Texas (8-14, 3-8). Tony Mitchell had 13 points, six rebounds and three blocked shots for the Mean Green. The Trojans won the earlier meeting between the schools 67-53 on Jan. 10 in Little Rock, Ark. White was the top scorer for UALR in that game with 16 points.
